Package: proxtop
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libvirt0, libncurses5 | libncurses6
Description: VM monitoring tool for KVM and Proxmox VE hypervisors
 proxtop (formerly kvmtop) monitors virtual machine resource utilization
 from the hypervisor level, measuring the real resource consumption
 including overhead.
 .
 Features:
  - Hypervisor-level metrics from /proc, libvirt, and QMP
  - CPU steal time and overhead detection
  - Noisy neighbor identification
  - Multiple output formats: ncurses, text, JSON
  - TCP streaming to monitoring systems
  - Auto-detection of KVM and Proxmox VE environments
 .
 This package contains the proxtop monitoring tool and proxprofiler
 statistical profiling tool.

